Shell beans or peas. Bring water to a boil in a 2-quart sauce-pan over high heat. Add beans or peas to boiling water; return to boiling. Cover, reduce heat, and cook 25 to 35 minutes for kernel beans, 20 to 30 minutes for limas, or 8 to 10 minutes for peas. Drain well; add salt and pepper. Toss with butter, if desired, and turn into serving dish.